# scandir() – List Files

`scandir(string $directory, int $sorting_order = SCANDIR_SORT_ASCENDING): array|false` returns an array of files and directories inside the given path. Includes `.` and `..`.

```php
$items = scandir('uploads');
foreach ($items as $item) {
    if ($item != '.' && $item != '..') {
        echo $item . "\n";
    }
}
```

# glob() – Find Pathnames Matching Pattern

`glob(string $pattern, int $flags = 0): array|false` finds pathnames matching a pattern (like `*.txt`).

```php
$txtFiles = glob('*.txt');
```

```php
<?php
// List all files in current directory excluding . and ..
$files = array_diff(scandir('.'), array('..', '.'));
print_r($files);

// Get all .jpg files
$images = glob('images/*.jpg');
print_r($images);
?>
```

# rmdir() – Remove Directory

`rmdir(string $directory): bool` removes an **empty** directory. If the directory is not empty, you must delete its contents first.

```php
if (rmdir('tempdir')) {
    echo "Directory removed.";
}
```

To delete a non-empty directory, you can write a recursive function or use external tools.

```php
<?php
function deleteDir($dir) {
    if (!file_exists($dir)) return true;
    if (!is_dir($dir)) return unlink($dir);
    foreach (scandir($dir) as $item) {
        if ($item == '.' || $item == '..') continue;
        if (!deleteDir($dir . DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR . $item)) return false;
    }
    return rmdir($dir);
}

deleteDir('old_folder');
?>
```
